---
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout title="Remove PII from Logs Locally - GigaSieve Guide" description="Mask emails, phone numbers, and IPs locally before sharing logs.">
    <section class="container mx-auto px-4 py-12 max-w-3xl">
        <nav class="text-sm text-slate-500 mb-6">
            <a href="/guides" class="hover:text-cyan-400">Guides</a>
            <span class="mx-2">/</span>
            <span class="text-slate-400">Remove PII</span>
        </nav>

        <h1 class="text-3xl font-extrabold text-slate-200 mb-4">Remove PII from Logs Locally</h1>
        <p class="text-slate-400 mb-8">
            Before sharing logs with vendors or colleagues, you should remove personally identifiable 
            information (PII). Here's how to do it safely without uploading anywhere.
        </p>

        <div class="bg-red-500/10 border border-red-500/30 rounded-xl p-6 mb-8">
            <h2 class="text-lg font-bold text-red-400 mb-2">[warn] Why this matters</h2>
            <p class="text-slate-400 text-sm">
                Logs often contain IP addresses, emails, user IDs, and session tokens. 
                Sharing these can violate GDPR, CCPA, and other privacy regulations.
            </p>
        </div>

        <h2 class="text-xl font-bold text-slate-300 mb-4">What counts as PII?</h2>
        <ul class="list-disc list-inside space-y-2 text-slate-400 mb-8">
            <li>IP addresses</li>
            <li>Email addresses</li>
            <li>Phone numbers</li>
            <li>User IDs and session tokens</li>
            <li>API keys and secrets</li>
        </ul>

        <h2 class="text-xl font-bold text-slate-300 mb-4">How GigaSieve helps</h2>
        <p class="text-slate-400 mb-6">
            Use the filter to identify lines containing PII patterns. In V2, we'll add 
            automatic masking features. For now, you can manually review and redact.
        </p>

        <div class="bg-emerald-500/10 border border-emerald-500/30 rounded-xl p-6 mb-8">
            <h2 class="text-lg font-bold text-emerald-400 mb-2">100% local</h2>
            <p class="text-slate-400 text-sm">
                GigaSieve never uploads your files. All analysis happens in your browser, 
                so your sensitive data never leaves your machine.
            </p>
        </div>

        <a href="/app" class="inline-flex items-center gap-2 bg-gradient-to-r from-emerald-500 to-cyan-500 text-white font-bold py-3 px-6 rounded-xl shadow-lg mb-8">
            Analyze Logs Locally ->
        </a>

        <h2 class="text-xl font-bold text-slate-300 mb-4">Related</h2>
        <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-4">
            <a href="/guides/regex-extract-from-log" class="bg-slate-900 hover:bg-slate-800 rounded-xl p-4 border border-slate-800">
                <h3 class="font-semibold text-slate-300">Regex Extract</h3>
            </a>
            <a href="/privacy" class="bg-slate-900 hover:bg-slate-800 rounded-xl p-4 border border-slate-800">
                <h3 class="font-semibold text-slate-300">Privacy Policy</h3>
            </a>
        </div>
    </section>
</Layout>
